   :file       "ADR-kotoba-shell-aiueos-safe-kotoba.md"
   :title      "kotoba-shell: Tauri の kotoba 版と aiueos / safe Kotoba の責務分離"
   :status     :proposed
   :date       "2026-06-28"
   :topics     #{:shell :tauri :clojure :clojurescript :wasm :aiueos :kotoba-wasm :safe-kotoba :capability :self-hosting :mobile :desktop :windows :macos :release :notarization :codesigning :smartscreen}
   :note       "Defines kotoba-shell as the app shell / WebView / native capability provider / packager layer. Separates kotoba as the language+database+semantic substrate, aiueos as the component OS/broker/capability graph, and kotoba wasm / safe Kotoba components as the executable app-logic layer. Records the self-hosting direction: Rust remains the bootstrap/substrate while language/admission semantics progressively move into Kotoba safe Wasm components. Adds the portable aiueos flavor split (core without wasm-runtime for verify/inspect; runner with embedded wasm-runtime for launch without global wasmtime/Node), macOS Developer ID/notarization release gates, and Windows Authenticode plus SmartScreen reputation gates. Implemented slice includes Target::Windows, windows build/export/verify/release-check/signing-check/submission-check artifacts, generated Windows security review helpers, and desktop aiueos portable release helpers (`aiueos-portable-plan.json`, `build-aiueos-core.bb`, `build-aiueos-runner.bb`). Initial dogfood target is manimani."}

