  {:id         :adr-kotoba-lang-profile
   :file       "ADR-kotoba-lang-profile.md"
   :title      "kotoba-lang language profile crate"
   :status     :accepted
   :date       "2026-06-29"
   :crate      "crates/kotoba-lang"
   :topics     #{:language :clojure :cljc :kotoba-lang :kotoba-clj :safe-kotoba :wasm}
   :artifacts  ["crates/kotoba-lang/src/lib.rs"
                "crates/kotoba-lang/README.md"
                "crates/kotoba-lang/resources/kotoba/lang/profile.edn"
                "crates/kotoba-lang/resources/kotoba/lang/conformance/manifest.edn"
                "crates/kotoba-cli/tests/public_cli.rs"
                "crates/kotoba-clj/tests/lang_profile_conformance.rs"
                "docs/lang/README.md"
                "docs/lang/coverage.edn"
                "docs/lang/versioning.md"
                "docs/lang/gates.md"]
   :note       "Splits the language profile/source compatibility contract from the compiler implementation. kotoba-lang owns accepted source extensions, reader targets, reader-conditional branch order, namespace extension priority, a machine-readable profile, M6 coverage metadata, and conformance fixtures. kotoba wasm is the public compile path for the Kotoba/EDN-subset to WebAssembly compiler; kotoba-clj remains the implementation crate and runs the manifest-driven conformance suite. .kotoba is the canonical Kotoba source extension, while portable .cljc remains the shared Clojure-family surface with #?(:kotoba ...) for Kotoba-specific branches."}

  {:id         :adr-kotoba-package-cid-lock
   :file       "ADR-kotoba-package-cid-lock.md"
   :title      "Kotoba package references, CID locks, and capability-safe dependencies"
   :status     :accepted-contract
   :date       "2026-06-30"
   :topics     #{:package :registry :cid :repo-rid :signature :safe-kotoba :capability :supply-chain :kotoba-cli :kotoba-rad}
   :artifacts  ["docs/ADR-kotoba-package-cid-lock.md"]
   :note       "Connects the standalone package contract from kotoba-lang/kotoba-lang (`lang/package.edn`) to the implementation workspace. Safe Kotoba dependencies must be locked by repo RID, signed manifest CID, source tree CID, signer DID, explicit capability grant set, transitive lock entries, and optionally reproducible component CID. Name plus semver without repo RID, signature, and CID pins is non-conforming for safe execution. Future kotoba-cli safe-build work should reject unsigned, version-only, not-CID-pinned, or over-capability dependencies; kotoba-rad/kotoba-git resolve repo identity and Git object CID bridges; kototama consumes already-verified HostCaps rather than deciding package authority."}

  {:id         :adr-repository-boundaries
   :file       "ADR-repository-boundaries.md"
   :title      "Repository boundaries and extraction policy"
   :status     :accepted
   :date       "2026-06-30"
   :topics     #{:repository :ownership :kotoba-lang :kotoba-cli :kami-engine :murakumo :kotodama :migration}
   :artifacts  ["README.md"
                "docs/ADR-repository-boundaries.md"]
   :note       "Keeps kotoba-lang/kotoba as the canonical language/runtime/database substrate while contracts are still co-evolving. Reserves kotoba-lang/kotoba-lang for the standalone language contract once an external compiler/runtime/package/conformance consumer exists; keeps the public kotoba crate/CLI in this workspace as an integration binary. Records kotodama extraction into kotoba-lang/inference, kotoba-lang/kotodama-host, kotoba-lang/kotodama-mcp, kotoba-lang/kotodama-cells, kotoba-lang/kotodama-py, and kotoba-lang/kotodama-holochain, leaving crates/kotoba-kotodama as a legacy redirect root. Routes hosting and operations to kotoba-lang/murakumo, domain actors to etzhayyim/com-etzhayyim-*, and AT Protocol app surfaces to gftdcojp/app-aozora. Defines split criteria: stable public contract, independent CI, external consumer or independent release cadence, named owner/gate, and only thin compatibility fixtures remaining in kotoba."}

  {:id         :adr-kotodama-cljc-num-torch-inference
   :file       "ADR-kotodama-cljc-num-torch-inference.md"
   :title      "kotodama CLJC inference uses torch + num"
   :status     :proposed
   :date       "2026-06-29"
   :repo       "https://github.com/kotoba-lang/inference"
   :crate      "kotoba-lang/inference"
   :topics     #{:kotodama :inference :cljc :torch :num :wgsl :webgpu :webgl :wasm}
   :artifacts  ["kotoba-lang/inference:deps.edn"
                "kotoba-lang/inference:cljc/src/kotodama/inference/runtime.cljc"
                "kotoba-lang/inference:cljc/src/kotodama/inference/ports.cljc"
                "kotoba-lang/inference:cljc/src/kotodama/inference/core.cljc"
                "kotoba-lang/inference:verify/maturity.edn"
                "kotoba-lang/inference:browser/README.md"
                "crates/kotoba-kotodama/inference/README.md"]
   :verify     "cd ../inference && clojure -M:verify-maturity-run && clojure -M:verify-maturity-run --include-local-model"
   :note       "Records that kotodama inference is CLJC-first over existing kotoba-lang/torch module graphs and kotoba-lang/num tensor compute. Transformers.js, ONNX, and ONNX Runtime Web are not runtime foundations. The primary browser and terminal path is torch-clj model graph plus num-clj WGSL/WebGPU/WASM compute; WebGL is only a host-provided num-compatible backend. verify/maturity.edn tracks the coverage and maturity gates, verify-torch-num proves the minimal torch graph to num tensor lowering boundary plus a two-layer :gemma4-block graph handoff to a custom num-backed host runner, verify-gguf reads the local gemma4:e4b GGUF artifact header/metadata/tensor directory/payload windows/F32 samples directly and verifies Q4_K attention/output/MLP dequantization samples plus Q6_K attention/MLP/token embedding dequantization samples and RoPE metadata, verify-gemma-num uploads those decoded real-model blocks into num-clj NDArrays, decodes the BOS token embedding row from the real GGUF tensor, applies blk.0 attention RMSNorm, evaluates partial blk.0 Q/K/V projections with num/dot plus partial Q/K RoPE, materializes head 0 Q/K/V, verifies head0 and all-head single-token GQA attention, verifies two-token causal GQA attention over the KV visible-token boundary, projects those attention outputs through real blk.0 attn_output rows including full-width head0-only and all-head output projections, applies blk.0 FFN RMSNorm, keeps the standalone full blk.0 gated MLP gate/up/down projection contract available under KOTODAMA_VERIFY_FULL_LAYERS=1, verifies a reusable two-block composer through blk.0 -> blk.1 with full block summaries for both blocks derived from the cached core/forward block result when KOTODAMA_VERIFY_FULL_LAYERS is greater than 1, skips the legacy standalone full MLP output generation on that multi-layer path, verifies the same real two-block contract through torch/run over indexed :gemma4-block layers and through core/forward over the IModelRuntime port with a verified repeated-call forward cache hit, applies output_norm RMSNorm, evaluates tied token_embd candidate logits plus full-vocabulary tied embedding logits, performs greedy/top-k sampling, and checks them through num reductions, and verify-maturity-run executes the required gates. Live local-model generation still uses the Ollama host adapter with gemma4:e4b identity/digest checks as operational evidence for the IModelRuntime generate boundary, not as the portable runtime foundation."}

